i'm trying to debug a vending machine controller written in verilog. it's a simple fsm that accepts coins (nickel=5c, dime=10c, quarter=25c) and dispenses when total >= 25c. but in simulation the state machine gets stuck in the 'dispense' state and never returns to idle.

here's the error from the simulator:
```
# ** Error: testbench.sv(42): timeout — FSM did not return to IDLE within 100 cycles
#    Time: 500 ns  Scope: tb_vending.uut
#    State at timeout: DISPENSE (3'b011)
#    coin_inserted=0, total=8'h19 (25 cents)
```

i've looked at the code but can't spot the issue:

```verilog
module vending_fsm (
  input clk, rst_n,
  input nickel, dime, quarter,
  output reg dispense
);
  localparam IDLE     = 3'b000;
  localparam ACCUM    = 3'b001;
  localparam DISPENSE = 3'b011;
  localparam CHANGE   = 3'b010;

  reg [2:0] state, next_state;
  reg [7:0] total, next_total;
  reg coin_inserted;

  always @(posedge clk or negedge rst_n) begin
    if (!rst_n) begin
      state <= IDLE;
      total <= 0;
    end else begin
      state <= next_state;
      total <= next_total;
    end
  end

  always @(*) begin
    coin_inserted = nickel || dime || quarter;
    next_state = state;
    next_total = total;
    dispense = 0;

    case (state)
      IDLE: begin
        if (coin_inserted) begin
          next_state = ACCUM;
          if (nickel)  next_total = total + 8'd5;
          if (dime)    next_total = total + 8'd10;
          if (quarter) next_total = total + 8'd25;
        end
      end
      ACCUM: begin
        if (total >= 8'd25)
          next_state = DISPENSE;
        else
          next_state = IDLE;
      end
      DISPENSE: begin
        dispense = 1;
        if (total > 8'd25)
          next_state = CHANGE;
        else
          next_state = IDLE;
        next_total = 0;
      end
      CHANGE: begin
        next_state = IDLE;
      end
    endcase
  end
endmodule
```

the testbench inserts a quarter at cycle 1, and the fsm goes idle->accum->dispense but then stays in DISPENSE forever. what could cause this? i don't have waveforms yet.
